<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!--
  ClaudeBar Sparkle appcast — BETA channel.

  Served via GitHub Pages at:
    https://beerbeatbox.github.io/claudebar/appcast-beta.xml
  Subscribed to by users who enable Settings > "Receive beta updates"; the app
  switches its feed URL to this file (lib/settings/prefs.dart). It carries beta
  (pre-release) builds AND every stable release, so opting in never holds a
  tester back from a stable update.

  Maintained by the release workflow: a beta release prepends here only; a
  stable release prepends to BOTH this file and appcast.xml. Do not hand-edit.

  PER RELEASE: prepend a fresh <item> inside <channel> (newest first). Get the
  edSignature + length from `rps ship` output (it runs sign_update on the zip),
  or run: dart run auto_updater:sign_update build/dist/ClaudeBar-X.Y.Z.zip

  Item template (copy, fill in, place directly below <language>):

    <item>
      <title>Version X.Y.Z</title>
      <sparkle:version>N</sparkle:version>
      <sparkle:shortVersionString>X.Y.Z</sparkle:shortVersionString>
      <sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>10.15.0</sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>
      <description><![CDATA[ <ul><li>What changed.</li></ul> ]]></description>
      <pubDate>Day, DD Mon YYYY HH:MM:SS +0000</pubDate>
      <enclosure
        url="https://github.com/beerbeatbox/claudebar/releases/download/vX.Y.Z/ClaudeBar-X.Y.Z.zip"
        sparkle:os="macos"
        sparkle:edSignature="PASTE_FROM_sign_update"
        length="PASTE_FROM_sign_update"
        type="application/octet-stream" />
    </item>

  Notes:
    * sparkle:version is CFBundleVersion = the pubspec build number (the +N).
      It is what Sparkle compares to decide "is there a newer build"; it MUST
      strictly increase every release. shortVersionString is display-only.
    * sparkle:minimumSystemVersion must be three-part (10.15.0, not 10.15).
    * length is bytes; sign_update computes it, do not hand-edit.
    * The enclosure points at the .zip release asset, not the .dmg.
-->
